<inglise> ANNEX I </inglise>
<eesti> I LISA </eesti>
<inglise> Labour force survey: definition of unemployment </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u vaatlus: t&ouml;&ouml;puuduse m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In accordance with the ILO standards adopted by the 13th and 14th International Conference of Labour Statisticians (ICLS), for the purposes of the Community labour force sample survey, unemployed persons comprise persons aged 15 to 74 who were: </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt 13. ja 14. t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;ustatistikute rahvusvahelisel konverentsil vastuv&otilde;etud ILO standarditele, loetakse &uuml;henduse t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u valikvaatluse l&auml;biviimisel t&ouml;&ouml;tuteks need 15-74-aastased isikud, kes: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) without work during the reference week, i.e. neither had a job nor were at work (for one hour or more) in paid employment or self-employment; </inglise>
<eesti> a) on t&ouml;&ouml;ta vaatlusn&auml;dala jooksul, s.t neil ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;kohta ning nad ei ole teinud palgat&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;i tegutsenud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana (&uuml;he tunni v&otilde;i rohkem); </eesti>
<inglise> (b) currently available for work, i.e. were available for paid employment or self-employment before the end of the two weeks following the reference week; </inglise>
<eesti> b) on t&ouml;&ouml;tajatena saadaval, s.t valmis alustama palgat&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;i tegutsemist f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana enne vaatlusn&auml;dalale j&auml;rgneva kahe n&auml;dala l&otilde;ppu; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) actively seeking work, i.e. had taken specific steps in the four week period ending with the reference week to seek paid employment or self-employment or who found a job to start later, i.e. within a period of at most three months. </inglise>
<eesti> c) otsivad aktiivselt t&ouml;&ouml;d, s.t on v&otilde;tnud konkreetseid meetmeid vaatlusn&auml;dalaga l&otilde;ppeva neljan&auml;dalase ajavahemiku jooksul, et leida palgat&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;i v&otilde;imalust hakata tegutsema f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana, v&otilde;i kes on leidnud t&ouml;&ouml;, millega alustatakse hiljem, s.t k&otilde;ige rohkem kolme kuu p&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of point 1(c), the following are considered as specific steps: </inglise>
<eesti> Punkti 1 alapunkti c t&auml;henduses loetakse konkreetseteks meetmeteks j&auml;rgmised toimingud: </eesti>
<inglise> - having been in contact with a public employment office to find work, whoever took the initiative (renewing registration for administrative reasons only is not an active step), </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;henduse v&otilde;tmine riikliku t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametiga, et leida t&ouml;&ouml;d, olenemata kumb osapool &uuml;hendust v&otilde;ttis (registreerimise uuendamist halduslikel p&otilde;hjustel ei k&auml;sitleta aktiivse toiminguna), </eesti>
<inglise> - having been in contact with a private agency (temporary work agency, firm specialising in recruitment, etc.) to find work, </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;henduses olemine era&otilde;igusliku t&ouml;&ouml;b&uuml;rooga (ajutist t&ouml;&ouml;d pakkuvad b&uuml;rood, t&ouml;&ouml;le v&auml;rbamisele spetsialiseerunud ettev&otilde;tted, jne), et leida t&ouml;&ouml;d, </eesti>
<inglise> - applying to employers directly, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&ouml;&ouml;rdumine taotlusega otse t&ouml;&ouml;andjate poole, </eesti>
<inglise> - asking among friends, relatives, unions, etc., to find work, </inglise>
<eesti> - otsinud t&ouml;&ouml;d s&otilde;prade, sugulaste, ameti&uuml;hingute jne kaudu, </eesti>
<inglise> - placing or answering job advertisements, </inglise>
<eesti> - pannud ajalehte t&ouml;&ouml;otsimiskuulutusi v&otilde;i vastanud t&ouml;&ouml;pakkumiskuulutustele, </eesti>
<inglise> - studying job advertisements, </inglise>
<eesti> - t&ouml;&ouml;pakkumiskuulutuste uurimine, </eesti>
<inglise> - taking a recruitment test or examination or being interviewed, </inglise>
<eesti> - osalemine t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmiskatsetel, -konkursil v&otilde;i -intervjuul, </eesti>
<inglise> - looking for land, premises or equipment, </inglise>
<eesti> - maa, ruumide v&otilde;i seadmete otsimine, </eesti>
<inglise> - applying for permits, licences or financial resources. </inglise>
<eesti> - taotluste tegemine ruumide, litsentside v&otilde;i rahaliste vahendite saamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Education and training are considered as ways of improving employability but not as methods of seeking work. </inglise>
<eesti> Haridust ja koolitust peetakse t&ouml;&ouml;alase konkurentsiv&otilde;ime suurendamise vahendiks, kuid mitte t&ouml;&ouml;otsimise viisiks. </eesti>
<inglise> Persons without work and in education or training will only be classified as unemployed if they are "currently available for work" and "seeking work", as defined in points 1(b) and (c). </inglise>
<eesti> Mittet&ouml;&ouml;tavaid isikuid, kes &otilde;pivad v&otilde;i osalevad koolituses, liigitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tuks &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui nad on "t&ouml;&ouml;tajatena saadaval" ja "otsivad t&ouml;&ouml;d" vastavalt punkti 1 alapunktide b ja c m&auml;&auml;ratlustele. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Lay-offs are classified as unemployed if they do not receive any significant wage or salary (significant is set at &gt;=50 %) from their employer and if they are "currently available for work" and "seeking work". </inglise>
<eesti> Koondatud isikud loetakse t&ouml;&ouml;tuks juhul, kui nad ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt saanud suuremat osa palgast (suuremaks osaks loetakse 50 % v&otilde;i rohkem) ja kui nad on "t&ouml;&ouml;tajatena saadaval" ja "otsivad t&ouml;&ouml;d". </eesti>
<inglise> Lay-offs are treated as a case of unpaid leave initiated by the employer - including leave paid out of government budget or by funds (16th ICLS). </inglise>
<eesti> Koondatud loetakse samav&auml;&auml;rseteks isikutega, kes on palgata puhkusel t&ouml;&ouml;andja ettepanekul, kaasa arvatud riigieelarvest v&otilde;i fondidest kompenseeritav puhkus (16. </eesti>
<inglise> In this case, lay-offs are classified as employed if they have an agreed date of return to work and if this date falls within a period of three months. </inglise>
<eesti> ICLS). Nimetatud juhul loetakse koondatud isikud t&ouml;&ouml;tajateks, kui nad on kokku leppinud t&ouml;&ouml;lemineku kuup&auml;eva ja see kuup&auml;ev j&auml;&auml;b l&auml;hema kolme kuu sisse. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> During the off-season, seasonal workers cannot be considered as having a formal attachment to their high-season job - because they do not continue to receive a wage or salary from their employer although they may have an assurance of return to work. </inglise>
<eesti> Hooajat&ouml;&ouml;lisi ei saa v&auml;ljaspool hooaega lugeda ametlikult seotuks nende hooajalise t&ouml;&ouml;ga, kuna nad ei saa t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt pidevat palka, kuigi v&otilde;ivad kindlad olla, et saavad t&ouml;&ouml;le tagasi p&ouml;&ouml;rduda. </eesti>
<inglise> If they are not at work during the off-season, they are classified as unemployed only if they are "currently available for work" and "seeking work", as defined in points 1(b) and (c). </inglise>
<eesti> Kui nad v&auml;ljaspool hooaega ei t&ouml;&ouml;ta, liigitatakse nad t&ouml;&ouml;tuks &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui nad on "t&ouml;&ouml;tajatena saadaval" ja "otsivad t&ouml;&ouml;d" vastavalt punkti 1 alapunktide b ja c m&auml;&auml;ratlustele. </eesti>
<inglise> ANNEX II </inglise>
<eesti> II LISA </eesti>
<inglise> Labour force survey: principles for the formulation of the questions on the labour status </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u vaatlus: h&otilde;iveseisundit k&auml;sitlevate k&uuml;simuste s&otilde;nastusp&otilde;him&otilde;tted </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The questions on the labour status according to the ILO definition (employed, unemployed or inactive) are in general the first questions in the individual questionnaire, immediately following the questions on the demographic characteristics of the household members. </inglise>
<eesti> ILO m&otilde;istetele vastavad h&otilde;iveseisundit k&auml;sitlevate k&uuml;simuste s&otilde;nastusp&otilde;him&otilde;tted (t&ouml;&ouml;taja, t&ouml;&ouml;tu v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu) on enamasti individuaalk&uuml;sitluste esimesed k&uuml;simused, neile j&auml;rgnevad kohe k&uuml;simused leibkonna liikmete demograafiliste andmete kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, they are not preceded by questions on the main or the usual activity (student, housekeeping, retired, etc.) or on the administrative status of a registration at the public employment office to claim unemployment benefits, where this would prejudice the response to the questions on the ILO labour status. </inglise>
<eesti> Neile ei tohiks eelneda k&uuml;simused peamise v&otilde;i tavap&auml;rase tegevuse kohta (&otilde;pilane, kodune, pension&auml;r jne) v&otilde;i k&uuml;simused riiklikus t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalituses t&ouml;&ouml;tu abiraha saamiseks registreeritud haldusliku seisundi kohta, kui need v&otilde;iksid m&otilde;jutada ILO h&otilde;iveseisundit k&auml;sitlevatele k&uuml;simustele vastamist. </eesti>
<inglise> In the case of dependent interviewing in later waves and when the labour status as an employed or inactive person is apparently permanent or stable, their labour status can be shortly verified with reference to their status in the previous wave. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu isiku h&otilde;iveseisund on ilmselt pidev v&otilde;i muutumatu, v&otilde;ib j&auml;rgnevate k&uuml;sitluste puhul nende h&otilde;iveseisundit kiiresti kontrollida eelnevates k&uuml;sitlustes m&auml;rgitud seisundi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The sequence of the questions on employment consists of at least two separate questions: one question on currently working and another question on having a job when being temporarily absent from work (persons on leave). </inglise>
<eesti> H&otilde;iveseisundit k&auml;sitlevaid k&uuml;simusi on v&auml;hemalt kaks: &uuml;ks k&uuml;simus selle kohta, kas isik t&ouml;&ouml;tab ja teine selle kohta, kas tal on t&ouml;&ouml;koht, kui ta ajutiselt ei t&ouml;&ouml;ta (puhkusel olevad isikud). </eesti>
<inglise> The question on being at work must precede the question on having a job so that the contrast between both questions contributes to a complete identification of the temporarily absent. </inglise>
<eesti> K&uuml;simus t&ouml;&ouml;tamise kohta peab eelnema k&uuml;simusele t&ouml;&ouml;koha omamise kohta, nii et nende kahe k&uuml;simuse v&otilde;rdlemise kaudu ilmneks selgesti mittet&ouml;&ouml;tamise ajutisus. </eesti>
<inglise> The identification of lay-offs (unpaid leave initiatied by the employer) and their classification as employed (or unemployed) persons depends on two conditions of a formal job attachment: an assurance of return to work after the end of the contingency and the short duration (&lt;=3 months) of the suspension of the labour contract. </inglise>
<eesti> Koondatute kindlakstegemine (palgata puhkus t&ouml;&ouml;andja ettepanekul) ja nende liigitamine t&ouml;&ouml;tajateks (v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tuteks) s&otilde;ltub kahest t&ouml;&ouml;suhete formaalsest tingimusest: on olemas kindel lubadus, et t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;ib p&auml;rast etten&auml;gematu olukorra l&otilde;ppu t&ouml;&ouml;le tagasi p&ouml;&ouml;rduda ning t&ouml;&ouml;leping on peatatud l&uuml;hiajaliselt (3 kuud v&otilde;i v&auml;hem). </eesti>
<inglise> Both conditions are determined by a question following the question about the reason for their temporary absence or the season why they did not look for a job in the previous four weeks or by response categories in these questions. </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;lema tingimuse olemasolu tehakse kindlaks k&uuml;simusega, mis j&auml;rgneb k&uuml;simusele isiku ajutise mittet&ouml;&ouml;tamise p&otilde;hjuste kohta v&otilde;i selle kohta, miks isik ei ole eelneva nelja n&auml;dala jooksul t&ouml;&ouml;d otsinud v&otilde;i nende k&uuml;simuste etteantud valikvastuste abil. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The questions on employment and job search must contain a cue for the identification of persons with a minor job of just a few or even one hour. </inglise>
<eesti> H&otilde;iveseisundit ja t&ouml;&ouml;koha otsimist k&auml;sitlevad k&uuml;simused peavad olema koostatud selliselt, et nende abil on v&otilde;imalik kindlaks teha v&auml;hese, isegi &uuml;hetunnise t&ouml;&ouml;ajaga isikuid. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The questions on employment must contain a cue for the identification of unpaid family workers. </inglise>
<eesti> H&otilde;iveseisundit k&auml;sitlevate k&uuml;simuste abil peab olema v&otilde;imalik kindlaks teha palgata t&ouml;&ouml;tavaid pereliikmeid. </eesti>
<inglise> Alternatively, they are identified by a separate question about being at work. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende kindlakstegemiseks v&otilde;ib kasutada ka eraldi k&uuml;simust t&ouml;&ouml;lk&auml;imise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The questions on employment must clearly indicate that only work for pay or profit is considered as an economic activity within the ILO framework. </inglise>
<eesti> H&otilde;iveseisundit k&auml;sitlevad k&uuml;simused peavad selgesti v&auml;ljendama, et ILO m&otilde;istes loetakse majandustegevuseks &uuml;ksnes palga v&otilde;i kasu eest tehtav t&ouml;&ouml;. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> The reference period of employment must be clearly specified. </inglise>
<eesti> H&otilde;iveseisundi vaatlusperiood tuleb selgesti m&auml;&auml;ratleda. </eesti>
<inglise> The question on employment refers as a rule to the last week, defined as "from Monday to Sunday", giving the exact date. </inglise>
<eesti> H&otilde;iveseisundit k&auml;sitlev k&uuml;simus k&auml;ib enamasti eelmise n&auml;dala kohta, see m&auml;&auml;ratletakse "esmasp&auml;evast p&uuml;hap&auml;evani" ja lisatakse t&auml;psed kuup&auml;evad. </eesti>
<inglise> The reference periods of job search and availability must be clearly specified. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;otsingute ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajana saadavaloleku vaatlusperiood tuleb selgesti m&auml;&auml;ratleda. </eesti>
<inglise> The two questions on job search and job search methods refer to the past four weeks including the reference week and the question on availability to the period until the end of the two weeks following the reference week. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;otsinguid ja t&ouml;&ouml;otsingute viise k&auml;sitlevad k&uuml;simused k&auml;ivad eelneva nelja n&auml;dala kohta, vaatlusn&auml;dal kaasa arvatud, ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajana saadavalolekut k&auml;sitlevad k&uuml;simused ajavahemiku kohta, mis l&otilde;peb kaks n&auml;dalat p&auml;rast vaatlusn&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise> 7. </inglise>
<eesti> 7. </eesti>
<inglise> All persons who were asked the questions on employment and were identified as having no job are asked the question on job search. </inglise>
<eesti> Isikule, kellele esitati k&uuml;simus h&otilde;iveseisundi kohta ja kelle puhul tehti kindlaks, et neil ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;kohta, esitatakse k&uuml;simus t&ouml;&ouml; otsimise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> No other filter question precedes this question. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellele k&uuml;simusele ei eelne &uuml;htegi filterk&uuml;simust. </eesti>
<inglise> In the case of dependent interviewing in later waves and when the labour status as an employed or inactive person is apparently permanent or stable, their labour status can be shortly verified with reference to their status in the previous wave. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu isiku h&otilde;iveseisund on ilmselt pidev v&otilde;i muutumatu, v&otilde;ib j&auml;rgnevate k&uuml;sitluste puhul nende h&otilde;iveseisundit kiiresti kontrollida eelnevates k&uuml;sitlustes m&auml;rgitud seisundi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> 8. </inglise>
<eesti> 8. </eesti>
<inglise> The question on job search must refer to any effort, even irregular, by the respondent to find a job or to establish her/his own business. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;otsinguid k&auml;sitleva k&uuml;simuse kaudu peab ilmnema, mida vastaja on ette v&otilde;tnud, kas v&otilde;i ajutiselt, et t&ouml;&ouml;kohta leida v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tlust alustada. </eesti>
<inglise> The wording of the question must avoid that only a continuous search throughout the entire reference period is considered as a sufficient condition of job search. </inglise>
<eesti> K&uuml;simuse s&otilde;nastus peab v&auml;listama v&otilde;imaluse, et piisavaks t&ouml;&ouml;otsimise tingimuseks loetaks &uuml;ksnes kogu vaatlusperioodi jooksul toimunud pidev t&ouml;&ouml;otsimine. </eesti>
<inglise> 9. </inglise>
<eesti> 9. </eesti>
<inglise> The question on job search methods must contain active and passive search methods. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;otsingu viise k&auml;sitlev k&uuml;simus peab h&otilde;lmama aktiivseid ja passiivseid otsinguviise. </eesti>
<inglise> The following are considered as active search methods: </inglise>
<eesti> Aktiivseks otsimisviisiks loetakse j&auml;rgmist: </eesti>
<inglise> - having been in contact with the public employment office to find work, </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;henduses olemine riikliku t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalitsusega, et leida t&ouml;&ouml;d, </eesti>
<inglise> - having been in contact with a private agency to find work, </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;henduses olemine era&otilde;igusliku t&ouml;&ouml;b&uuml;rooga, et leida t&ouml;&ouml;d, </eesti>
<inglise> - applying to employers directly, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&ouml;&ouml;rdumine taotlusega otse t&ouml;&ouml;andjate poole, </eesti>
<inglise> - asking among friends, relatives, trade unions, etc., to find work, </inglise>
<eesti> - t&ouml;&ouml; otsimine s&otilde;prade, sugulaste, ameti&uuml;hingute jne kaudu, <hi rend="sub"> F </hi> </eesti>
<inglise> - placing or answering job advertisements, </inglise>
<eesti> - ajalehte t&ouml;&ouml;otsimiskuulutuste panemine v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;pakkumiskuulutustele vastamine, </eesti>
<inglise> - studying job advertisements, </inglise>
<eesti> - t&ouml;&ouml;pakkumiskuulutuste uurimine, </eesti>
<inglise> - taking a recruitment test or examination or being interviewed, </inglise>
<eesti> - osalemine t&ouml;&ouml;lev&otilde;tmiskatsetel, -konkursil v&otilde;i -intervjuul, </eesti>
<inglise> - looking for land, premises or equipment, </inglise>
<eesti> - maa, ruumide v&otilde;i seadmete otsimine, </eesti>
<inglise> - applying for permits, licenses of financial resources. </inglise>
<eesti> - taotluste tegemine ruumide, litsentside v&otilde;i rahaliste vahendite saamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 10. </inglise>
<eesti> 10. </eesti>
<inglise> The "contact with the public employment office to find work" is a two-way contact. </inglise>
<eesti> "&Uuml;henduses olemine riikliku t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalitsusega, et leida t&ouml;&ouml;d" on kahepoolne toiming. </eesti>
<inglise> It can be initiated by the registered unemployed person or by the employment office. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendust v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta nii registreeritud t&ouml;&ouml;tu kui t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalitus. </eesti>
<inglise> This contact must be included as the first (response category in the) question on job search methods. </inglise>
<eesti> See &uuml;hendusev&otilde;tmine peab kajastuma esimeses t&ouml;&ouml;otsimise viise k&auml;sitlevas k&uuml;simuses (v&otilde;i selle etteantud valikvastustes). </eesti>
<inglise> It is distinct from the administrative renewal of a registration to claim unemployment benefits (when this was not preceded by a spell of employment or inactivity). </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;hendusev&otilde;tmist tuleb eristada t&ouml;&ouml;tu abiraha saamise taotluse registreerimise halduslikust uuendamisest (kui sellele ei eelnenud ajavahemik, mil isik t&ouml;&ouml;tas v&otilde;i oli t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu). </eesti>
<inglise> It is also distinct from the assistance provided by the employment office to improve the employability of the registered unemployed person. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda tuleb eristada ka t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalituse p&uuml;&uuml;etest aidata parandada registreeritud t&ouml;&ouml;tu t&ouml;&ouml;alast konkurentsiv&otilde;imet. </eesti>
<inglise> The "contact with the public employment office to find work" as an active step only involves: </inglise>
<eesti> "&Uuml;henduses olemine riikliku t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalitsusega, et leida t&ouml;&ouml;d" aktiivse toiminguna t&auml;hendab &uuml;ksnes: </eesti>
<inglise> - putting the respondent's name in the employment office file for the first time (after a spell of employment or inactivity), </inglise>
<eesti> - vastaja esmakordset registreerimist t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalituses (t&ouml;&ouml;tamise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse perioodi j&auml;rel), </eesti>
<inglise> - finding out about possible job vacancies, or </inglise>
<eesti> - v&otilde;imalike vabade t&ouml;&ouml;kohtade v&auml;ljaselgitamist, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - "at the initiative of the employment office a suggestion of a job opportunity", which may be accepted or refused by the job searcher. </inglise>
<eesti> - t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ivetalituse algatust t&ouml;&ouml;koha pakkumiseks, mille t&ouml;&ouml;otsija v&otilde;ib vastu v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i mitte. </eesti>
<inglise> 11. </inglise>
<eesti> 11. </eesti>
<inglise> Job search methods are enumerated until at least three active methods have been mentioned. </inglise>
<eesti> T&ouml;&ouml;otsimisviise loetletakse, kuni v&auml;hemalt kolm aktiivset otsimisviisi on nimetatud. </eesti>
<inglise> 12. </inglise>
<eesti> 12. </eesti>
<inglise> Persons who are currently not employed and who are not looking for a job because they have already found a job which will start later, i.e. within a period of at most three months must be identified as a separate category. </inglise>
